  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "couName": "CPB use",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). A screening sensitivity study was conducted informally across the five flow-speed operating points to confirm that the relative hemolysis index ranking was stable under ±10% perturbations to inlet boundary conditions; findings were incorporated into the rationale for model inputs and test conditions factors. No structured uncertainty quantification campaign was deemed necessary beyond this screening exercise given the MRL 2 classification.",
